Why do people hate css so much?!?!
Why is the solution to styling components to throw out css?<p>I thought BEM and other css frameworks/conventions solved this problem.<p>For example:<p><pre><code>  myComponent/myComponent.jsx
  myComponent/myComponent.css
</code></pre>
in myComponent.css<p><pre><code>  .myComponent {
    /* whatever */
  }
</code></pre>
Since all of your components are uniquely named(I hope), you can just use flat single class selectors without any specificity issues.
